<br>
So if they gave you what you want for your class you'd STOP playing? Hence then don't so they can get more money?<br>
<br>
Sorry but that makes no sense whatsoever. <br>
<br>
They give what they think will make the game more enjoyable for the majority of players so they can keep their player base as large as possible. This may or may not be what any one individual class or even the majority of players are asking for. They use their own judgement about what they think that is.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 454<br> <font color=#000000>(6/29/03 6:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ack</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure Mythic is looking at the causes of the problems with the games, which I feel they should be.<br>
<br>
Although they have effectively said &quot;if a class or realm is not having many players, we'll upgrade it&quot; which I feel is very wrong, particularly being an Albion tank, if this is really how they rig their game. If I'm one of hundreds, does this mean myself and my friends have to be the 'Indiana Jones Nazis' and are INTENDED to be mowed down?<br>
<br>
I think Mythic should go read online message-boards actross the entire internet and just look for themselves at what the problems are. We're seeing the same three or four things being repeated over and over again. I'm not going to flip out over Mythic's abscence of fixing the  problems, because they're steadily growing like a cancer, and Mythic is soon going to operate or lose a lot of customers.<br>
<br>
My true thoguhts are that releasing add-ons to retain customers in teh face of SWG and that other online RPG wasn't the smartest move to make. They should have just addressed class balance issues.<br>
<br>
Yes, there are a lot of people playing as the 'overpowered' classes. But there are actually more people playing the classes which suffer  day-in, day-out, because of this.<br>
<br>
Assassins ---- everyone else. Enchanters ----- everyone else.<br>
<br>
Those were just two examples. If they fixed the inherent problems they would be making a lot of people say Thank You Mythic, and maybe for three people, it would be the end of the world.<br>
<br>
I'd actually like to see them fixing the 'zerging' problem on the UK servers by creating one (or even two!) more servers, and alowing people to utilise a /charshift command to &quot;move house&quot;. I know I would.<br>
